580
00:31:48.585 --> 00:31:50.251
- South Dakota's
biggest industry

581
00:31:50.335 --> 00:31:53.543
has always been agriculture...

582
00:31:53.627 --> 00:31:56.418
but it's done by fewer
and fewer farmers.

583
00:31:58.293 --> 00:32:01.543
So the little towns
that support farm families

584
00:32:01.627 --> 00:32:02.835
often wither.

585
00:32:10.502 --> 00:32:13.251
- My dad has a number
of little quips.

586
00:32:13.335 --> 00:32:14.251
One of his sayings is.

587
00:32:14.335 --> 00:32:15.460
"Farming is a great way
of life

588
00:32:15.543 --> 00:32:17.126
as long as you don't have
to make a living at it."

589
00:32:21.293 --> 00:32:22.877
I've wanted to farm
my whole life.

590
00:32:22.960 --> 00:32:24.960
That's all I ever wanted
to do.

591
00:32:27.168 --> 00:32:29.919
My dad told me and had
the foresight to know

592
00:32:30.001 --> 00:32:32.251
that our farm is fairly close
to Sioux Falls

593
00:32:32.335 --> 00:32:34.377
and may or may not be here
in the future.

594
00:32:34.460 --> 00:32:36.210
It will likely be developed
at some point in time.

595
00:32:36.293 --> 00:32:39.752
He said I had to get
a real job.

596
00:32:39.835 --> 00:32:43.085
- Karl Oehlke's real job
when he's not farming

597
00:32:43.168 --> 00:32:46.085
is as a physician's assistant
at a Avera Health.

598
00:32:46.168 --> 00:32:49.627
Knowing the stress farmers
are constantly under.

599
00:32:49.710 --> 00:32:54.001
whether from flooded fields
or low commodity prices.

600
00:32:54.085 --> 00:32:58.669
Karl helped create
the Farmer's Stress Hotline.

601
00:32:58.752 --> 00:33:00.794
- It's 24 hours a day.
It's confidential.

602
00:33:00.877 --> 00:33:02.418
Talking to me on the phone.

603
00:33:02.502 --> 00:33:04.460
I can empathize with them
and explain to them.

604
00:33:04.543 --> 00:33:06.919
"Yeah. I know exactly
what you're going through."

605
00:33:07.001 --> 00:33:09.126
The biggest thing
we're dealing with right now--

606
00:33:09.210 --> 00:33:11.293
fear. anxiety.

607
00:33:11.377 --> 00:33:12.919
"I'm working extremely hard.

608
00:33:13.001 --> 00:33:14.418
"yet I have nothing to show
for it.

609
00:33:14.502 --> 00:33:17.502
How can I keep my kids
in shoes?"

610
00:33:17.585 --> 00:33:18.752
Trying to prevent suicide.

611
00:33:18.835 --> 00:33:20.418
is. of course.
our biggest concern.

612
00:33:22.251 --> 00:33:26.377
Prototypical farmer was always
the stereotype of a very stoic.

613
00:33:26.460 --> 00:33:28.460
hardened person. you know?

614
00:33:28.543 --> 00:33:30.001
And to let their guard down

615
00:33:30.085 --> 00:33:31.835
is not something
that they're used to doing.

616
00:33:35.585 --> 00:33:38.043
I've heard so many farmers
say to me

617
00:33:38.126 --> 00:33:39.460
even by the end
of the interview

618
00:33:39.543 --> 00:33:42.502
and maybe I haven't even
offered them a medication.

619
00:33:42.585 --> 00:33:44.335
they just felt better talking.

620
00:33:44.418 --> 00:33:48.210
It's just like this sense
