1175
01:03:31.669 --> 01:03:33.293
That was Africa.
That was our honeymoon.

1176
01:03:33.377 --> 01:03:35.293
- It was a giant rat.
- Yeah.

1177
01:03:35.377 --> 01:03:37.794
We knew it bonded us
as a family

1178
01:03:37.877 --> 01:03:40.126
when we did a lot of this
travel with our little kids.

1179
01:03:40.210 --> 01:03:42.168
We were a unit.
and sink or swim.

1180
01:03:42.251 --> 01:03:43.210
we were in this together.

1181
01:03:43.293 --> 01:03:44.627
We had to figure it all out.

1182
01:03:53.877 --> 01:03:55.752
- Historically.
geographically.

1183
01:03:55.835 --> 01:03:57.627
very difficult
to get through here.

1184
01:04:00.919 --> 01:04:02.043
People that came over here.

1185
01:04:02.126 --> 01:04:03.669
they were okay
with being isolated.

1186
01:04:03.752 --> 01:04:05.001
They had to be.

1187
01:04:05.085 --> 01:04:08.543
If you have
a tougher kind of person...

1188
01:04:08.627 --> 01:04:11.210
There was a poet laureate.
Louise McNeill.

1189
01:04:11.293 --> 01:04:14.502
She wrote a book called
"Gauley Mountain."

1190
01:04:14.585 --> 01:04:17.627
The very last poem in it.
it says the people here

1191
01:04:17.710 --> 01:04:21.794
"now possess the last dark
current of the wilderness."

